  ./COVERAGE.md:336:| `commons-codec:commons-codec` | [1.10<br>- 1.22.0](metadata/commons-codec/commons-codec/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Commons Codec provides implementations of common encoders and decoders such as Base64, hexadecimal, phonetic, and digest utilities. It helps Java applications transform binary and text data using standard encoding, hashing, and checksum algorithms.</details> | [100.0% (5/5 calls)](stats/commons-codec/commons-codec/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:762:| `org.apache.activemq:artemis-commons` | [2.28.0<br>- 2.37.0](metadata/org.apache.activemq/artemis-commons/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ActiveMQ Artemis Commons provides shared Java utility classes, buffer abstractions, exceptions, JSON helpers, and concurrency support used across Apache ActiveMQ Artemis components. It supplies the common runtime building blocks that Artemis clients, servers, and related modules rely on for core messaging infrastructure behavior.</details> | [97.4% (74/76 calls)](stats/org.apache.activemq/artemis-commons/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:808:| `org.apache.directory.api:api-util` | [1.0.0<br>- 2.1.8](metadata/org.apache.directory.api/api-util/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Directory LDAP API Utilities provides shared helper classes for the Apache Directory LDAP API, including string and Unicode processing, hexadecimal and Base64 handling, generalized time parsing, collections, reflection, and OSGi helpers. It is a Java utility module used by the broader Directory API components rather than a standalone LDAP client or server.</details> | [100.0% (3/3 calls)](stats/org.apache.directory.api/api-util/) |
